  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STEM Education for Girls and Women in Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Cameroon, only 1 in 10 female students are in the Vocational and University STEM course. This is not an encouraging disparity, as Cameroon aspires to be an emerging economy in 2035. This aggressive goal demands educational gender equity in STEM fields. This project will provide scholarships and materials to well-qualified girls and women from rural areas to attend Vocational and University STEM courses to build a diverse workforce needed for today&apos;s and tomorrow&apos;s best job opportunities.</narrative>
  </description>
